body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Express. My name is Tyler Diaz. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, Tyler. My name is Gloria Jackson.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Gloria. Can I have your phone number for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five dash eight two one dash six three four five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And may I have your email address next, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it is gloria dot jackson at email dot com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing your contact details, Gloria. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you, Tyler, for your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Gloria. Thank you for reaching out to Car Express. Have a great day!
